sub_title: Master in Educational Sciences. Educational Psychologist. Personal Development, Life Coaching, Trainer.
summary:
I am an Educational Psychologist with a Masters in Education passionate about my profession and with the work I have done during the past twenty years. 
 
My academic training as psychologist, specialized in education with a master's degree in educational sciences has given me tools and knowledge to follow educative process, evaluate, analyze, plan, implement, guide, assess and support learning processes; diagnose and intervene in learning disabilities; identify academic and social behavior and treat difficulties. 

I have been part of multidisciplinary teams formed by psychologists, teachers, neurologists, physical and speech therapists and special educators and have worked with small groups as well as with individuals using different strategies, methods and resources. 

I very much like to work in an educational environment enjoying the challenge of discovering in each member their individuality, needs and particular processes. I am a very sociable person easily adaptable to new environments, trustworthy, capable to manage delicate information with respect and responsibility.   My ability to communicate has enabled me to have excellent interaction with colleagues, students, parents and teachers.
